The paper deals with measuring the impact of academic books using online reviews, which involves natural language processing and sentiment analysis. This falls under the sub-categories of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper also involves data mining and machine learning techniques, which are relevant to Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Digital Libraries (cs.DL), and Cybersecurity (cs.CY).
